“Keep pushing”

Starting at the bottom with nothing and building your way up to the top is an incredible journey filled with hardships, challenges, and valuable lessons. It takes grit, determination, and resilience to persevere through the obstacles that come your way. It's about learning from your mistakes and using them as stepping stones to success. You develop a sense of humility, gratitude, and appreciation for every opportunity that comes your way. It's not just about reaching the top, but also about the personal growth, strength, and character that you gain along the way. So keep pushing, keep striving, and never give up on your dreams, for every step you take towards the top is a testament to your strength and resilience. 

( and I spelled LASTSUSPECT wrong 😑🤣) Nothing in life is perfect 👊🏽

Want to go viral? Here’s how! (Read on)
•
•
1. 3-9 Seconds: This is pretty simple... keep it as short as possible. Remember the goal is to go viral. If you TRULY want to go viral, take it from me, KEEP IT SHORT.

2. Trending Songs: The algorithm will work very completely in your favor and help you push ANY content that has a trending song playing in it. Some “experts” say you must also do the trend that follows the song and not just have the song playing but, take it from me... having tried and tested both, just having the song playing is enough.

Use 🎧 for better listening experience :) shoutout @richardzphotoz for the pointers.

I know this has nothing to do with photography and y’all will probably hate on this post buttttttt Yesterday @marilynhue surprised me with the best birthday gift I’ve ever had! She got me private lessons at drifting school @driftday . Start of a new career? Yuppppppp Here’s a tiny recap of what I got. Shot on my GoPro, I was too excited hahah lfgggg! Also my first time ever driving manual 😳😳😳😱🤗
POV : you’re riding your bicycle through downtown LA.
Need a new adventure, were we goinggggg?

Who would have thought… will you marry me would be coming out of my mouth ! From a friendship born on a reality tv show to me proposing to my best friend and partner in crime. As soon as I met her I just knew I wanted to spend the rest of my life with her. I packed up my stuff and moved my life across the United States leaving everything I knew and betting on us and myself. I had this entire speech planned and when it came time I couldn’t even speak my mind I completely blacked out and was on auto pilot to the point where I thought I was about to pass out 🤣  it was a perfect mess! We’ve done so much in the past two and a half years. Between traveling around the world, work and all the fun stuff our bond got stronger and stronger everyday. I’m happy , I’m thankful and I can’t wait to grow and see what the future holds for us. @marilynhue I’m in love with you! Let’s fucking goooooooooo! ( you can hear what I say in her post ) 🙇🏽‍♂️

Why is money a fake people magnet?

Share this with someone… 

Have you ever found yourself wondering where the passionate photographer in you has gone? 

If you’ve been doing photography long enough and have met people of the same interest, you would have seen this happen a lot. 

One minute, you see a person spewing out images every day as if they do nothing else but shoot. 

Then, another minute, you see them dropping the craft entirely, selling or giving away their gear. 

But why does this happen? 

#losangeles #travel #igreel #foryoupage #cinematic

I have come to accept the feeling of not knowing where I am going. 

 I have trained myself to love it.

 You may not know where you’re going, 

but you know that so long as you spread your wings,
